===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# a [[lime]] and [[water]] [[mixture]] for [[painting]] walls and [[fence]]s [[bright]] [[white]].
#: '''Quotations'''
#:* '''1952''': For walls plaster gave a smooth white surface; or if it was not sufficiently white, or had become discoloured, it could be brightened up with a coat of whitewash or paint. &mdash; L.F. Salzman, ''Building in England'', p. 157.
# A [[victory]] without reply

